    Gronda is a text editor inspired by the Aegis Display Manager editor 
    found on Apollo workstations. 

SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS

    Unix/Linux or Mac OS X
    FLTK 1.3 for the graphical interface
    ncurses for the terminal interface (currently not working)

COMMANDS

!            Bang
"num"        Go to line number "num"
=            Position
[row,col]    Go to row and column
//           Forward Search
ad           Arrow Down
al           Arrow Left
ar           Arrow Right
au           Arrow Up
ce           Create Edit
dr           Define Region
echo         Highlight Text (-r for rectangular)
ed           Delete Character
ee           Edit Erase
ei           Insert/Overstrike
en           Enter Newline
er           Enter Raw
es           Enter String
kd           Key Definition
lineno       Line numbers on/off
mouse        Mouse to Text Cursor on/off
msg          Message to output window
pb           Pad Bottom
ph           Pad Horizontal
pn           Pad Name
pp           Pad Page
pt           Pad Top
pv           Pad Vertical
pw           Pad Write
pwd          Print Working Directory
ro           Read Only
sic          Set Insert Cursor
tb           To Bottom
tdm          To DM
tl           To Left
tn           To Next Pad
tr           To Right
tt           To Top
wc           Window Close
xc           Copy (-r for rectangular)
xd           Cut (-r for rectangular)
xp           Paste (-r for rectangular)